Product name: Victorian 9ct Gold Onyx Mourning Brooch (with original hair)
Description:
Victorian 9ct Yellow Gold Onyx Mourning Brooch (with original hair)
Front loading glass panel
Pin and 'C' catch
Unmarked but tested as 9ct gold
Length = 2.4cm
Gross weight = 5.2 grams
Victorian women used to wear mourning jewellery when mourning the loss of a loved one or family member. The use of woven hair was commonplace, although exquisite pieces such as this one would only have been worn by the upper classes, as they were the only ones who could have afforded such things.
This beautiful example has been made in 9ct gold and has been set with 12 black onyx stones. The original woven hair remains.
Condition = Excellent. The original hair and glass panel are in tact and unmarked; there are no chips to the Onyx stones.

Product name: Craft Ginger Beer Kit - "create your own homemade Ginger Beer" soft drink - Refreshment
Description:
= A Perfect Gift for ginger beer lovers & budding brewers alike =
Each kit contains enough culture, sugar and ginger (with instructions) to make your own traditional ginger beer "plant." The plant is so called because it will provide you with an ongoing supply of 9 pints of ginger beer a week, a wonderful flavoursome soft drink alternative to beer in the evening. The full recipe and instructions included is a tried and tested traditional method to make a classic British ginger beer with ground ginger.
How does it work?
Simply feed your “plant” with ground ginger and granulated sugar every day for one week. At the end of the week the concentrated liquid from the plant is strained off and is made up with sugar, water and lemon juice to make the finished ginger beer, the process is made easy and no special equipment is needed. Once you have made your ginger beer you have the option to start the plant all over again, why not spread the love and give half to a friend to make their own? The instructions include details of how to start a new plant all over again whenever you feel like it.
What is the ginger beer like?
Ginger beer is a fermented drink made using yeast, the fermentation adds characteristic flavour to the ginger beer and the final product is less than 0.5% alcohol so please be assured that our ginger beer is a flavoursome soft drink. If you are diabetic you can still enjoy the ginger beer by making your final drink with “Splenda” in place of sugar.
Quality Garantee
Our recipe has been tried and tested over generations. In making our kits we are conscious to use only fair-trade sugar and high quality ground ginger. All ingredients are dried and have an excellent shelf life.
Delivery
We endeavor for all kits to be delivered within 1 week of purchase within the UK.
Airmail delivery to the USA takes 5-7 working days and Europe takes 3-5 working days on top of packing and shipping arrangements.
For Christmas USA orders -  Please order before 10th December to ensure we can catch the last posting day for Christmas delivery
For Christmas UK order -  Please order before 21st December to ensure we can catch the last posting day for Christmas Delivery.
